<Base title="SEO Audit Swansea | Full Site Analysis | SEO Swansea" description="Professional SEO audit for Swansea businesses covering technical health, on-page optimisation, backlink profile, local SEO, and competitor analysis with a prioritised action plan." schema={schema}>

  <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">Home</a>
    <span class="mx-1">/</span>
    <a href="/services/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">Services</a>
    <span class="mx-1">/</span>
    <span class="text-gray-700">SEO Audit</span>
  </nav>

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-brand mb-4">SEO Audit for Swansea Businesses</h1>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">An SEO audit is a thorough look under the bonnet of your website. We examine five critical areas — technical health, on-page optimisation, off-page authority, local SEO presence, and competitor positioning — to show you exactly why your site ranks where it does. More importantly, we give you a prioritised action plan so you know precisely where to focus your budget and effort for the biggest gains in visibility and revenue right here in Swansea.</p>

  <div class="bg-rose-50 border-l-4 border-accent p-4 rounded-r-lg my-6">
    <p class="font-medium text-text mb-1">Quick Answer</p>
    <p class="text-text/80">An SEO audit digs into your website's technical health, content quality, backlink profile, local SEO, and competitive landscape. For Swansea businesses, it pinpoints the exact fixes needed to climb Google's rankings and attract more local customers. A full audit takes 5 to 10 working days and starts from £500.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Most Swansea business owners know their website could do better in search but have no idea where to start. Sound familiar? That's exactly what an audit is for. Instead of chasing random tips from blog posts or making changes based on gut feeling, you get a data-driven picture of where you stand and a clear roadmap to improve. Whether you're based at Swansea Marina, Wind Street, SA1 Waterfront, or Enterprise Park in Llansamlet, the audit is shaped around your market, your location, and the competitors you're actually up against.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We audit websites of all sizes — from five-page brochure sites for sole traders in Mumbles to large online shops and multi-location service businesses across Swansea Bay. The method stays the same, but the depth scales to match the complexity of your site and how competitive your market is.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">What's Included in the Audit</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every audit we run covers five pillars. Each one looks at a different angle of your search performance, and together they paint a complete picture of where you are and what needs to change.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Technical SEO Analysis</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We crawl every page with Screaming Frog and cross-reference the findings with your Google Search Console data. This uncovers broken links, redirect chains and loops, duplicate content, missing or muddled canonical tags, robots.txt errors, XML sitemap problems, and Core Web Vitals failures. We test speed on mobile and desktop, check your HTTPS setup, and make sure your site is fully crawlable and indexable. For a deeper dive into this area, see our <a href="/technical-seo-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">technical SEO service page</a>.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">On-Page SEO Review</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We go page by page through your titles, meta descriptions, and heading hierarchy to check length, keyword use, and click-through appeal. We assess content quality, looking at word count, keyword relevance, topical depth, duplicate content, and thin pages. We also review internal linking to make sure your most important pages are getting enough link equity and that the overall site structure makes sense for both visitors and search engines.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Off-Page and Backlink Analysis</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Using Ahrefs, we pull your full backlink profile to assess the quantity, quality, and relevance of sites linking to you. We flag toxic or spammy links that might be dragging your rankings down, identify your strongest referring domains, and compare your profile against your top Swansea competitors. This tells us whether you need more links, need to disavow harmful ones, or should focus on earning links from specific local and industry-relevant sources.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Local SEO Assessment</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">For Swansea businesses that serve local customers, the local SEO pillar is often the one that drives the most revenue. We audit your Google Business Profile for completeness and accuracy, check NAP consistency across online directories and citations, review your local schema markup, and gauge your visibility in Google's local pack and map results. We also look at local landing pages for the areas you cover, whether that's Mumbles, Sketty, Morriston, Uplands, or the broader Swansea Bay region.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Competitor Analysis</h3>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We identify your top three to five organic competitors in Swansea and dig into what they're doing differently. That means comparing keyword rankings, content depth, backlink profiles, technical performance, and local SEO signals. The competitor analysis shines a light on gaps and opportunities — showing you exactly where rivals are weak and where you can overtake them with targeted improvements.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">The Audit Process</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Our audit follows a clear process designed to be thorough without getting in the way of your day-to-day. Here's how it works from start to finish.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Step 1: Discovery and Access</h3>
  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We start with a short questionnaire about your business, target audience, key services, and where you sit within Swansea. Then we ask for read-only access to your Google Search Console, Google Analytics, and Google Business Profile. If you don't have those set up yet, we'll get them configured as part of the audit at no extra cost.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Step 2: Data Collection</h3>
  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We run a full crawl of your website, pull 16 months of Search Console data, export your backlink profile from Ahrefs, and gather competitor intelligence. This phase usually takes a day or two and doesn't need any involvement from you.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Step 3: Analysis</h3>
  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Our team manually works through the data across all five audit pillars. We don't just hand you an automated report. While the tools generate the raw numbers, the analysis, prioritisation, and recommendations come from people who understand the Swansea market and the quirks of local search.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Step 4: Report Delivery</h3>
  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">You receive a written report covering all findings, a spreadsheet listing every issue with severity ratings and suggested fixes, and a prioritised action plan. Each recommendation is labelled critical, high, medium, or low priority so you know exactly where to start.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-brand-light mt-8 mb-3">Step 5: Walkthrough Call</h3>
  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We book a 30-minute video call to walk through the findings, answer your questions, and talk about what to do next. This makes sure you understand not just what needs fixing but why each change matters and how it ties back to your business goals in the Swansea market.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">What You Get</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every audit includes the following, delivered as a mix of PDF, spreadsheet, and shared documents.</p>

  <ul class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
    <li>Executive summary highlighting the three most impactful findings and recommended actions</li>
    <li>Full technical health report covering crawlability, indexation, speed, and security</li>
    <li>On-page analysis with page-by-page title, meta, heading, and content recommendations</li>
    <li>Backlink profile report with toxic link identification and link-building opportunities</li>
    <li>Local SEO scorecard covering Google Business Profile, citations, and local schema</li>
    <li>Competitor benchmark comparing your performance against the top Swansea competitors</li>
    <li>Prioritised action plan with issues ranked by impact and effort</li>
    <li>30-minute video walkthrough call</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Who Needs an SEO Audit</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">An audit is useful for any Swansea business with a website, but there are some situations where it becomes especially important.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>New websites.</strong> If you've just launched a site for a Swansea business, an early audit makes sure your technical foundations are right from day one. Sorting issues in the first few months is far easier and cheaper than untangling problems that have built up over years.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Website redesigns and migrations.</strong> Redesigns and platform moves are the single most common cause of dramatic ranking drops. An audit before migration sets your baseline, and one afterwards catches anything the changeover introduced. We've seen Swansea businesses lose 80 percent of their organic traffic after a redesign because redirects weren't mapped properly or canonical tags got muddled.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Ranking drops.</strong> If your Google rankings have suddenly fallen off a cliff, an audit is the quickest way to work out whether the culprit is a technical issue, an algorithm update, a penalty, or a competitor stepping up. Without one, you're guessing — and guessing wastes time and money fixing the wrong thing.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>New businesses in SA1, Enterprise Park, and Swansea Bay.</strong> Businesses setting up in Swansea's commercial hubs need solid online visibility from the start. An audit of your initial website ensures you're not carrying hidden technical debt that'll slow your growth in local search. Whether you're a tech startup at SA1 Waterfront or a trade business at Enterprise Park in Llansamlet, getting the foundations right early saves real money later.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Businesses that have never been audited.</strong> If your website is more than two years old and has never had a professional once-over, it's almost certainly picked up technical issues, stale content, and missed opportunities that are quietly costing you rankings and revenue.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Pricing</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Audit pricing depends on the size and complexity of your website. Small brochure sites with under 50 pages start from £500. Medium sites with 50 to 500 pages typically fall between £750 and £1,200. Larger or more complex websites are quoted individually. Every audit includes the full five-pillar analysis and walkthrough call described above.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">For a complete breakdown of audit and ongoing SEO service pricing, visit our <a href="/seo-pricing-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">SEO pricing page</a>.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Full Audit vs Free Audit</h2>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">We offer both a comprehensive paid audit and a <a href="/free-seo-audit-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">free SEO audit</a>. The free version is an automated health check that flags headline issues like site speed, mobile usability, basic on-page factors, and common technical errors. It's a handy starting point that gives you a snapshot of your site's health in minutes.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">The full paid audit goes much deeper. It's done by hand by our team, covers all five pillars including competitor analysis and local SEO, digs through 16 months of Search Console data, reviews your entire backlink profile, and produces a written report with a prioritised action plan. The paid audit uncovers issues that automated tools simply can't spot — things like content cannibalisation, internal link equity imbalances, and strategic gaps relative to your Swansea competitors.</p>

  <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">Not sure which you need? Start with the <a href="/free-seo-audit-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">free audit</a>. It'll give you enough information to decide whether a full audit makes sense for your business.</p>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8 text-center">
    <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-2">Want to find out exactly what's holding your Swansea website back?</p>
    <p class="text-text/80 mb-4">Start with a free audit or book a full analysis with a prioritised action plan.</p>
