  <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-text mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2">What exactly does an SEO audit cover for a Swansea business?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mt-2">A full audit looks at five areas: technical health (speed, crawlability, indexation, HTTPS), on-page optimisation (titles, meta descriptions, headings, content quality), off-page analysis (backlink profile, referring domains, toxic links), local SEO (Google Business Profile, citations, local schema), and competitor analysis. You get a prioritised report showing exactly what to fix and in what order.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2">How many days should we allow for the audit?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mt-2">For a typical Swansea business site with up to 100 pages, allow 5 to 7 working days. Bigger sites with hundreds or thousands of pages, like e-commerce stores or directories, can take up to two weeks. You get the full written report plus a 30-minute call to walk through the findings together.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2">What's the going rate for an SEO audit in Swansea?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mt-2">Pricing starts from £500 for small business websites. The final figure depends on how many pages you have, how complex your CMS is, and whether you want competitor analysis included. Check our <a href="/seo-pricing-swansea/" class="text-accent hover:underline font-medium">pricing page</a> for full details or drop us a line for a custom quote.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2">How's the free audit different from the paid version?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mt-2">The free audit is an automated health check that flags headline issues like speed, mobile usability, broken links, and basic on-page factors. The paid audit is a hands-on, in-depth analysis covering all five pillars, with a detailed written report, a spreadsheet of every issue, and a strategy call. The paid version catches things automated tools simply miss.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2">Does the audit actually fix problems, or just list them?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mt-2">The audit identifies and prioritises problems but doesn't include fixing them. We give you clear, actionable steps your developer or team can follow. If you'd like us to handle the fixes, we offer that separately or as part of an ongoing retainer. Plenty of Swansea businesses start with the audit and then move to a monthly plan for implementation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-text py-2">How often should we be getting an SEO audit done?</summary>
      <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mt-2">We suggest a full audit at least once a year, with lighter quarterly check-ins between. You should also run one after any big website change like a redesign, CMS migration, or domain move. If your rankings suddenly tank, an audit is the fastest way to work out whether it's a technical problem or a Google algorithm shift.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

